1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper deals with image processing and reconstruction, which falls under the purview of computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed algorithm can be seen as a machine learning approach to estimate the orientation parameters of the projection-images. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a novel algorithm for solving a specific problem in cryo-electron microscopy, which can be categorized under data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper deals with the reconstruction of 3D models from 2D images, which is a common problem in computer graphics. 
5. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper uses numerical experiments to demonstrate the efficacy of the proposed method, which falls under the purview of numerical analysis.
